[The initial report of contamination of a widely distributed pasta salad
with shigella bacteria is followed by more than 100 reports of clinical
disease so far, with the possibility of more cases. This type of foodborne
outbreak is a good example of the problems of centralized food preparation
with repackaging in spreading contaminated food and difficulties in
identifying the vehicle. The infectious dose of shigella is very low,
sometimes fewer than 200 organisms. Shigellosis presents with classical
bacillary dysentery with high fever and frequent diarrheal stools
containing blood and mucus. - Mod.LL]
